  "text": "In this study, w e found that the m ean of Adiponectin level in breast cancer patients (3.85 + 1.25 µg/ml) was lower compared to the mean of Adiponectin level in FAM patients (6.17 + 2.79 µg/ml) and was statistically significant with p = 0.017. This study result was similar to the result by [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , and Chen (2005) who have found significant correlation between Adiponectin level and breast cancer [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] 10) . The former researchers used patients that had negative mammography results as control, while in this study, the control group was patients with benign breast tumor which was confirmed to be F AM by histopathology.",
